excerpt: Events center with grand ballrooms, used for conventions & traditional performing arts events.
detail_description: Kurhaus Wiesbaden GmbH is a stunning Neoclassical building with Art Nouveau elements, including a magnificent metal and glass dome. The venue hosts high-profile events, conventions, and traditional performing arts shows. It also houses Wiesbaden's prestigious casino and an upscale restaurant. Adjacent to the Kurhaus is the picturesque Kurpark, a public park known for its English landscape design, featuring a lake with boat rentals and an impressive 6-meter tall fountain.
name: Kurhaus Wiesbaden GmbH

excerpt: Hessian state-run museum with collections of local history & varied art & natural history exhibits.
detail_description: Museum Wiesbaden is a prominent cultural institution in the heart of Wiesbaden, Germany. It houses a diverse range of exhibits that cater to various interests. The museum's three wings feature collections of local history, art from the 19th and 20th centuries, antiquities from the House of Nassau, and an impressive array of zoological specimens and fossils.
name: Museum Wiesbaden

excerpt: Established in 1852, this landscaped English-style park features a fountain & a lake with boats.
detail_description: Kurpark, also known as "Spa Park" in German, is a picturesque public park located in the heart of Wiesbaden, Germany. Established in 1852, this English-style landscape park boasts a serene lake where visitors can rent boats and a striking 6-meter tall fountain. It is often hailed as the most stunning park in Wiesbaden and offers a tranquil retreat from city life with its lush gardens, charming sculptures, and peaceful walking paths.
name: Kurpark

excerpt: 245-m. hill with a seasonal funicular & 19th-century church, plus a climbing course & hiking trails.
detail_description: Neroberg is a 245-meter hill in Wiesbaden, offering a variety of attractions. At the top sits St. Elizabeth's Church, a stunning Russian Orthodox church with panoramic city views. The hill also features a vineyard, restaurants, a pool, and hiking trails. Visitors can experience the historic Neroberg Mountain Railway, Germany's oldest water ballast-driven cog-and-rack railway.
name: Neroberg

excerpt: Longtime water cable rack & pinion railway running since 1888, providing picturesque hilltop vistas.
detail_description: Nerobergbahn Wiesbaden is a historic water-powered funicular railway that has been operating since 1888. It stands as the oldest water-propelled railway in Germany and one of the few in the world still using this unique propulsion system. The charming cable car offers a picturesque journey to the hilltop, providing spectacular views overlooking Wiesbaden. Visitors can enjoy a ride on two distinctively colored carriages and explore attractions such as St.
name: Nerobergbahn Wiesbaden

excerpt: Charming public square known for its open-air fountain that is fed by an underground hot spring.
detail_description: Kochbrunnen is a renowned hot spring in Wiesbaden, known for its open-air fountain located on a charming public square. The spring emerges at a scorching 66°C and has been recorded since the 14th century. The water is filtered through a processing plant before being channeled to the square, where visitors can also find a drinking water fountain under a Neo-Baroque pavilion.
name: Kochbrunnen

excerpt: This lavish baroque estate was home to princes and dukes of Nassau until the year 1841.
detail_description: Biebrich Palace, located in Wiesbaden, Germany, is a stunning Baroque-style estate that served as the residence for princes and dukes of Nassau until 1841. Commissioned by George August, Count of Nassau-Idstein in the early 18th century, it later became property of the Nassau-Ussingen dynasty. The palace is now utilized for conferences and ceremonies by the Hessian state government.
name: Biebrich Palace

detail_description: Located in the historic spa town of Wiesbaden, Germany, the Kaiser-Friedrich-Therme is a luxurious thermal bath that pays homage to the city's ancient founders. Built in 1910 in Art Nouveau style and adorned with a 4-million-euro mosaic, this establishment offers a variety of amenities across its 1,450 square meters.
name: Kaiser-Friedrich-Therme

detail_description: Evangelische Kindertagesstätte der Marktkirchengemeinde is a Protestant daycare center located in a central area. The facility, which has four groups, provides a spacious and uncrowded environment for children to enjoy. It is highly praised by parents who appreciate the dedicated team and the enjoyable experience their children have at the daycare center.
name: Evangelische Kindertagesstätte der Marktkirchengemeinde

excerpt: Musicals, operas & plays are performed in this opulent destination dating from 1894.
detail_description: Hessisches Staatstheater Wiesbaden, located on Christian-Zais-Strasse 3, is a historic theater dating back to 1894 and is considered one of the most stunning theaters in Germany. This opulent destination hosts a diverse program from September to June, featuring operettas, musicals, ballets, and plays. The International May Festival is a highlight with concerts, classical in-house drama productions, and guest performances by renowned theater companies.
name: Hessisches Staatstheater Wiesbaden

excerpt: Guided tours are available of this 19th-century Neoclassical palace, now home to government offices.
detail_description: Wiesbaden City Palace, a 19th-century Neoclassical palace located in the heart of Wiesbaden, was originally intended to be the residence of Duke William of Nassau. Although it was completed after his death in 1841, the palace has had a rich history, serving as a government office and even becoming a second home for Prussian Kaisers. Today, it houses the Hessian State Parliament and offers guided tours for visitors interested in its historical significance.
name: Wiesbaden City Palace

excerpt: Apple strudel, Sachertorte, waffles & pancakes, plus breakfast, at an ornate coffeehouse from 1859.
detail_description: Café Maldaner GmbH is an ornate coffeehouse located in Wiesbaden, offering a variety of delectable treats such as apple strudel, Sachertorte, waffles, and pancakes. Established in 1859, this charming café exudes an old Viennese style decor that transports visitors back in time.
name: Café Maldaner GmbH

detail_description: The Ev. Marktkirchengemeinde u. Kirchenvorstand is a striking Protestant church that graces the skyline of Wiesbaden with its impressive five red brick spires, completed in 1862. Its neo-Gothic architectural style offers a captivating contrast to the city's classical buildings, making it a notable landmark for visitors exploring this charming German city.
name: Ev. Marktkirchengemeinde u. Kirchenvorstand

detail_description: Wilhelmstraße is the primary shopping thoroughfare in Wiesbaden, offering a blend of contemporary retail outlets and charming historic edifices. It's an ideal location for leisurely walks while admiring the city's diverse architectural styles.
name: Wilhelmstraße

detail_description: The Holocaust Memorial (Shadow of former Synagogue) in Wiesbaden, Germany, serves as a poignant tribute to the Jewish lives lost during the Holocaust. Situated near Michelsberg Hill, it spans both sides of a bustling street. One side features an interactive screen recounting the harrowing history of the Holocaust, while the other side lists victims' names, birthdates, and dates of death.
name: Holocaust Memorial (Shadow of former Synagogue)

detail_description: Taunusstraße is a charming street known for its well-preserved historicist house facades. Strolling along this picturesque thoroughfare offers a glimpse into the past, with architectural gems lining the way. Visitors can also take a leisurely break at one of the numerous inviting cafes dotted along the street, adding to the delightful experience of exploring Taunusstraße.
name: Taunusstraße

excerpt: Printing & book museum with Gutenberg Bibles by the 15th-century inventor of movable type printing.
detail_description: Nestled in the charming old quarter of Mainz, the Gutenberg Museum stands as a testament to the revolutionary impact of Johannes Gutenberg, the pioneer behind movable type printing. Established in 1900 to commemorate his 500th birthday, this museum is one of the oldest dedicated to printing and attracts visitors from around the globe.
name: Gutenberg Museum

excerpt: Mainz is a German city on the Rhine River. It’s known for its old town, with half-timbered houses and medieval market squares. In the center, the Marktbrunnen is a Renaissance fountain with red columns. Nearby, a distinctive octagonal tower tops the Romanesque Mainz Cathedral, built of deep red sandstone. The Gutenberg Museum honors the inventor of the printing press with exhibits, including 2 of his original bibles.
detail_description: Mainz, a charming German city situated along the picturesque Rhine River, is renowned for its well-preserved old town featuring traditional half-timbered houses and medieval market squares. The city's center boasts the impressive Marktbrunnen, a Renaissance fountain adorned with striking red columns, as well as the distinctive octagonal tower crowning the Romanesque Mainz Cathedral constructed from deep red sandstone.
name: Mainz

excerpt: Built in 1855, the city's only Russian Orthodox church & gilt domes were featured on postage stamps.
detail_description: St Elizabeth's Church, built in 1855, is the only Russian Orthodox church in the city and is known for its striking gilt domes. Situated atop Wiesbaden's Neroberg hill, it offers a breathtaking view of the city. The church was constructed by Duke Adolf of Nassau as a tribute to his late wife, Grand Duchess Elizabeth Mikhailovna of Russia. The church also houses her grave and is surrounded by the largest Russian cemetery in Europe outside of Russia.
name: St Elizabeth's Church

detail_description: Altstadt, located near the central market square, is home to a museum and beautifully restored buildings that were heavily bombed during World War II. Visitors can start their exploration at Marktplatz and wander through charming streets surrounding the cathedral.
name: Altstadt

excerpt: Gambling complex in an 18th-century building with slots, table games & an upmarket restaurant.
detail_description: Spielbank Wiesbaden is an 18th-century building that has been turned into a gambling complex. The casino features a variety of slot machines and table games, as well as an upscale restaurant. It is surrounded by beautiful parks and other buildings. Although the actual casino occupies only a small part of the building, it can get busy at times, which may result in waiting for tables. Nonetheless, overall it provides a pleasant experience due to its welcoming staff and nice ambiance.
name: Spielbank Wiesbaden

detail_description: The Wiesbadener Casino-Gesellschaft is one of the oldest casinos in Germany, boasting ornate and old-fashioned architecture that creates a unique atmosphere. The building, completed in 1874, houses some of the most beautiful event locations in the city. Its noble rooms and pompous Rococo lobby add to its charm. Additionally, it serves as a wonderful venue for weddings and other special events, with a dedicated team ensuring that every moment is magical for couples.
name: Wiesbadener Casino-Gesellschaft

detail_description: St. Bonifatius Church in Wiesbaden is a visually stunning Gothic-style masterpiece with an impressive exterior that transports you to another era. The detailed facade and majestic towers are truly breathtaking, although the interior may not match the grandeur of the outside. Despite this, it still offers a beautiful and quiet atmosphere for self-reflection and prayer. Visitors can admire the beautiful sculptures inside and experience a sense of wonder at the craftsmanship of these magnificent places of worship.
name: St. Bonifatius, Wiesbaden

detail_description: Warmer Damm is a charming public park located near Kurpark in the heart of the city. It features a lovely pond and several scenic trails, making it an ideal spot for leisurely strolls and picnics. The park is also home to the impressive Hessisches Staatstheater Wiesbaden, offering visitors a chance to appreciate its stunning architecture. With its tranquil atmosphere, it's perfect for unwinding with a good book or simply enjoying the natural surroundings.
name: Warmer Damm

excerpt: 1800s neo-Gothic brick church featuring a landmark main spire with a 49-bell carillon.
detail_description: The Evangelical Market Church in Wiesbaden, Germany is a stunning neo-Gothic brick church with a landmark main spire housing a 49-bell carillon. Despite significant damage during WWII, the church has undergone multiple restoration projects and stands as the tallest building in Wiesbaden. Its five impressive red towers dominate the skyline and the sound of its hand-pulled bells resonates throughout the city.
name: Evangelical Market church Wiesbaden

detail_description: Goldgasse, located in the heart of Wiesbaden, is a narrow street lined with an array of restaurants, tapas bars, and cafes. It offers a mix of high-end dining options as well as casual eateries where visitors can enjoy coffee or beer. The ambiance exudes a Mediterranean flair reminiscent of the Latin Quarter in Paris.
name: Goldgasse

detail_description: Nerotal-Anlagen is a tranquil park located near the Nerobergbahn, offering a peaceful retreat from the city's hustle and bustle. This century-old park features ponds with ducks, a children's play area, and even resident parakeets. It is wheelchair accessible and provides ample parking. Visitors can enjoy various activities such as cycling, inline skating, or simply taking a leisurely stroll while admiring the stunning views. The park also offers entertainment for families and is pet-friendly.
name: Nerotal-Anlagen

detail_description: Bäckerbrunnen "Die Altstadtkneipe" in Wiesbaden is a cozy and welcoming restaurant and bar located in the heart of the city. The atmosphere is quaint and quiet, making it a perfect spot for a relaxing evening. The friendly staff speaks English and provides excellent service, guiding guests through the menu options. While the menu may be slightly limited due to current circumstances, the food is delicious, with dishes like onion schnitzel standing out as particularly exceptional.
name: Bäckerbrunnen „Die Altstadtkneipe“

detail_description: Schlossplatz, or Castle Square, is the vibrant heart of Wiesbaden, steeped in history and charm. This picturesque town square is surrounded by stunning architecture, including the impressive Stadtschloss (city palace), Rathaus (town hall), and Marktkirche (market church). Throughout the year, Schlossplatz buzzes with life as it hosts a variety of special events and gatherings that draw both locals and visitors alike.
name: Schlossplatz

detail_description: Neroberg is a popular destination that offers a breathtaking view of the city. Visitors can take a funicular ride to reach the top and enjoy the panoramic scenery, making it a favorite spot for both locals and tourists. It's recommended to bring along a camera and perhaps some snacks for a small picnic. Whether you're traveling with family and friends or exploring solo, Neroberg provides a serene atmosphere that's perfect for capturing memorable moments.
name: Neroberg

detail_description: Greek-Orthodox Church Saint Georgios, also known as the Church of Saint Elizabeth, is a serene and spiritual attraction located in Wiesbaden, Germany. This beautiful church was built in the early 20th century and features stunning icons. The annual celebration of Georgios is a remarkable event with enthusiastic participation. The church's spiritual ambiance makes it a must-visit destination for those seeking tranquility and cultural experiences in Wiesbaden.
name: Greek-Orthodox Church Saint Georgios

detail_description: Tier-Reha Mainz, located beyond Wiesbaden's northwest boundary, has a rich history dating back to the 18th century when it was used as a pheasant breeding ground for hunts. The hunting lodge built in the 1740s still stands and now houses a restaurant. After World War II, the park reopened as an animal attraction featuring regional species.
name: Tier-Reha Mainz

detail_description: Altes Rathaus, the oldest building in Wiesbaden, dates back to 1610 and continues to serve as a functional structure. Initially constructed as a Town Hall, it now operates as a Registry Office while retaining its charm for both locals and visitors. Its simple yet sturdy architecture makes it a popular spot for photography and admiration. Situated on Schlossplatz, this historic building also accommodates the representative rooms of the Hessischer Landtag.
name: Altes Rathaus

detail_description: St. Elizabeth in Wiesbaden is home to a stunning Russian Orthodox church with five golden domes that shine in the sunlight. The sandstone structure also includes a parsonage and the largest Russian cemetery outside of Russia. Additionally, it houses a former Franciscan monastery that was inaugurated in 1936 and underwent significant reconstruction in 1989/90, featuring an altar and crucifixion group by Munich artist Hubert Elsasser. The community at St.
name: St. Elizabeth (parish seat)

detail_description: Tier One Analytics GmbH is a cutting-edge data analytics company that specializes in providing advanced analytical solutions to businesses. The company offers a wide range of services including data analysis, predictive modeling, and business intelligence. Tier One Analytics GmbH is known for its innovative approach to solving complex business problems using data-driven insights. With a team of experienced data scientists and analysts, the company helps clients harness the power of their data to make informed decisions and drive business growth.
name: Tier One Analytics GmbH

excerpt: Wiesbaden is a city in the western German state of Hesse. Its neoclassical Kurhaus now houses a convention center and a casino. The Kurpark is an English-style landscaped garden designed in 1852. The red, neo-Gothic Market Church on Schlossplatz is flanked by the neoclassical City Palace, seat of State Parliament. Museum Wiesbaden displays expressionist paintings by Alexej von Jawlensky and natural history exhibits.
detail_description: Wiesbaden, a city in the state of Hesse, Germany, is known for its neoclassical architecture and beautiful gardens. The Kurhaus, once a spa house, now serves as a convention center and casino. The Kurpark is an elegant English-style garden dating back to 1852. Visitors can admire the red neo-Gothic Market Church and the neoclassical City Palace on Schlossplatz.
name: Wiesbaden

excerpt: Early 20th-century villa restored as a work of art with tours & art events including barefoot tours.
detail_description: Schloss Freudenberg is a restored villa from the early 20th century which has been transformed into a work of art. The museum offers tours and art events, including barefoot ones. Visitors can enjoy interactive exhibits that stimulate their senses and enhance their understanding of physics. Although parking along the main road can be challenging, there may be other options available.
name: Schloss Freudenberg

detail_description: Gebr. Stern GmbH is a renowned destination for purchasing traditional German souvenirs and gifts, including cuckoo clocks, nutcrackers, beer steins, and other artisan products. The store offers a wide selection of handmade items from Germany and provides excellent customer service with knowledgeable and friendly staff. Visitors have praised the store for its extensive range of options for cuckoo clocks, including battery-operated and mechanical ones. Additionally, customers appreciate the convenience of shipping purchases internationally.
name: Gebr. Stern GmbH

excerpt: Eclectic concert venue, nightclub & independent cinema in a converted warehouse by rail tracks.
name: Kulturzentrum Schlachthof Wiesbaden e.V.

detail_description: In June 2021, the Opelbad outdoor bath provided a delightful experience for visitors with young children. The facilities were well-maintained and easily accessible, featuring a small wading pool and a large swimming pool. Despite the potential for crowding, there was ample space to relax and enjoy picnics amidst breathtaking views. While the water initially felt chilly in the morning, it became more comfortable by 10am.
name: Opelbad

excerpt: Modern center hosting conferences, trade fairs, exhibitions and events, offering event management.
detail_description: The RheinMain CongressCenter is a contemporary facility that serves as a hub for conferences, trade fairs, exhibitions, and various events. It offers comprehensive event management services and has gained a reputation as an exceptional venue for conferences. Visitors have praised its impeccable organization and cleanliness over the years. The friendly and helpful staff, particularly those in charge of building booths, have consistently provided assistance whenever needed.
name: RheinMain CongressCenter

detail_description: Located just outside the Mainz Cathedral, the Marktbrunnen is a Renaissance fountain that forms part of the charming historical attraction at Marktplatz. This market square, founded in the 10th century, was rebuilt after heavy bombing in WWII, with the fountain being one of the few original structures that remained intact. Built in the 16th century and highly ornamented, it sits at one corner of the lovely market plaza.
name: Marktbrunnen

excerpt: Ornate Renaissance hunting lodge with a modern glass roof, hosting corporate events & weddings.
detail_description: Jagdschloss Platte is an elaborate hunting lodge from the Renaissance period, now transformed into a versatile event space for corporate functions and weddings. It boasts a contemporary glass roof that adds a modern touch to its ornate structure. The interior features sections of the original walls, while stairs lead to a breathtaking view of the surrounding forest. During an after-conference event, delectable cuisine was served across various food stations where dishes were freshly prepared.
name: Jagdschloss Platte

excerpt: This forested island provides campgrounds, white sand beaches, playgrounds, sports fields & a cafe.
detail_description: Rettbergsaue, a small recreational island nestled between Mainz and Wiesbaden, offers a picturesque setting for outdoor activities. The island features campgrounds, white sandy beaches, playgrounds, sports fields, and a cafe/kiosk. While the beach is adorned with duck poop in some areas, the knee-deep water makes it safe for children to play under supervision.
name: Rettbergsaue

detail_description: Lutherkirche in Wiesbaden is a stunning church known for its beautiful concerts and unique features. The church houses the impressive Walcker organ, a national treasure monument from 1911, which offers fantastic acoustics for performances. Visitors can enjoy concerts featuring works by renowned composers like Cesar Franck and are encouraged to contribute to the collection box at the end of the show. Additionally, guided tours of the tower are available, providing an interesting experience for visitors.
name: Lutherkirche Wiesbaden

excerpt: Animal park in a former royal hunting reserve, with native plants, a petting zoo & pheasantry.
detail_description: Located just outside downtown Wiesbaden, Germany, Zoo and garden Fasanerie is a former royal hunting reserve that offers a nature hike experience with native plants and various animals. It's not a traditional zoo but rather a place for families to enjoy nature walks, visit the petting zoo, and observe animals like sheep, bunnies, roosters, deer, birds, and other wildlife.
name: Zoo and garden Fasanerie

excerpt: Refined space in a grand building hosting contemporary & classic operas, musicals & plays.
detail_description: The Mainz State Theater, also known as Staatstheater Mainz, is a prestigious cultural institution located in the heart of Mainz, Germany. Housed in a grand 19th-century building, it features three distinct performance spaces: the opera house, playhouse, and studio stage. The theater offers a diverse program of contemporary and classic operas, musicals, and plays. Visitors have praised the high-quality performances and innovative programming.
name: Mainz State Theater

detail_description: If you're looking for an exhilarating adventure, TIXS Live Escape Rooms is the perfect destination! Gather your friends or family and dive into a world of mystery where teamwork is key to escaping. With rooms designed with meticulous attention to detail, you'll encounter a variety of creative puzzles that will challenge your wits and bring you closer together. Whether you're freeing a fridge stocked with chocolate, beer, and champagne or tackling other engaging scenarios like "Enterbt," there's something for everyone.
name: TIXS Live Escape Rooms
